Loans Dataset Exploration¶

by Ahmed Soliman¶

Preliminary Wrangling¶

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

This data set contains 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, borrower rate (or interest rate), current loan status, borrower income, and many others.

n_CreditGrade = df['CreditGrade'].value_counts().sum()
In [20]:
# ploting the variable
base_color = sb.color_palette()[0]
sb.countplot(data=df2, x='CreditGrade', color=base_color,
order=CreditGrade_order);

# get the current tick locations and labels
locs, labels = plt.xticks(rotation=90)

# loop through each pair of locations and labels
for loc, label in zip(locs, labels):
    # get the text property for the label to get the correct count
    count = CreditGrade_counts[label.get_text()]
    pct_string = '{:0.1f}%'.format(100*count/n_CreditGrade)
    # print the annotation just below the top of the bar
    plt.text(loc, count+2, pct_string, ha = 'center', color =
'black')

The most common credit grade across the profiles in loans dataset is C

Loan Original Amount Vs Is Borrower Homeowner Vs Available Bank Card Credit¶

In [41]:
def mean_poly(x, y, bins = 10, **kwargs):
    # set bin edges if none or int specified
    if type(bins) == int:
        bins = np.linspace(x.min(), x.max(), bins+1)
    bin_centers = (bin_edges[1:] + bin_edges[:-1]) / 2        
    # compute counts
    data_bins = pd.cut(x, bins, right = False,include_lowest = True)
    means = y.groupby(data_bins).mean()
    # create plot
    plt.errorbar(x = bin_centers, y = means, **kwargs)
    
bin_edges = np.arange(500, df2['LoanOriginalAmount'].max()+500, 1000)
g = sb.FacetGrid(data = df2, hue = 'IsBorrowerHomeowner', size = 5)
g.map(mean_poly, "LoanOriginalAmount", "AvailableBankcardCredit", bins = bin_edges)
g.set_ylabels('mean(AvailableBankCardCredit)')
g.add_legend()
